---
import BaseLayout from '../app/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'; import UploaderHero from '../widgets/uploader-hero/UploaderHero.astro'; import SeoLinksGrid from '../widgets/seo-links-grid/SeoLinksGrid.astro';
const title='Private Image Resizer and Compressor'; const description='Resize and compress images online in your browser. Preview the result, control dimensions and file size, then download without uploading your image.';
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description}><UploaderHero/><section class="intro"><div><span class="eyebrow">Private by design</span><h1>Resize and compress images without the upload</h1></div><p class="intro-copy"><strong>A practical image resizer for work that should stay private.</strong>See the picture before processing, choose exact dimensions or a file size, and download a clean JPEG, PNG, or WebP result.</p></section><section class="proof" aria-label="Product benefits"><article><b>01</b><h2>Local processing</h2><p>The browser reads and resizes your image on this device. There is no transfer queue and no remote copy to remove later.</p></article><article><b>02</b><h2>Visible result</h2><p>A real preview confirms that the correct file is selected. Original dimensions and file weight remain easy to check.</p></article><article><b>03</b><h2>Precise control</h2><p>Set width and height, preserve the aspect ratio, change format, or compress images toward a maximum file size.</p></article></section><SeoLinksGrid/><section class="section editorial"><div><span class="eyebrow">A calmer workflow</span><h2 class="section-title">Image resizing should be predictable</h2></div><div class="columns"><div><p>Online image tools often begin with a long upload and end with a download whose quality is hard to judge. This image resizer takes a more direct route. Your browser opens the source, displays it inside the workspace, applies the dimensions you choose, and creates the finished file locally.</p><p>That approach is useful for photographs, screenshots, product images, banners, scans, and signatures. It also keeps the original image away from an unknown server. Local processing does not make every file harmless, but it removes an unnecessary transfer from a common editing task.</p></div><div><p>The compressor works with JPEG and WebP quality when a maximum file size matters. For PNG files, the image resizer preserves the lossless format and can reduce dimensions when the selected limit cannot be reached through encoding alone.</p><p>You can keep the original proportions or enter a different canvas size. Exact presets cover common social dimensions, while file size presets help with forms and publishing systems that reject large images.</p></div></div></section><section class="section steps"><div class="section-heading"><div><span class="eyebrow">Three clear steps</span><h2 class="section-title">From source image to finished download</h2></div></div><ol><li><span>1</span><div><h3>Choose and inspect</h3><p>Select a JPEG, PNG, or WebP file. The preview appears immediately, together with its name and current file size.</p></div></li><li><span>2</span><div><h3>Set the output</h3><p>Enter dimensions, keep the aspect ratio linked if needed, then choose an output format and an optional maximum weight.</p></div></li><li><span>3</span><div><h3>Resize and save</h3><p>The image resizer processes every pixel in the browser. When compression is complete, the new image downloads to your device.</p></div></li></ol></section></BaseLayout>
<style>.proof{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);margin-top:1rem;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--radius);background:#fff}.proof article{padding:1.5rem}.proof article+article{border-left:1px solid var(--line)}.proof b{color:var(--blue);font-size:.72rem}.proof h2{margin:.65rem 0 .35rem;font-size:1.05rem}.proof p{color:var(--ink-soft);font-size:.86rem}.editorial{display:grid;grid-template-columns:.65fr 1.35fr;gap:4rem;padding:3rem;border-radius:var(--radius-lg);background:var(--ink);color:#fff}.editorial .eyebrow{color:var(--lime)}.columns{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:2rem}.columns p{color:#c6ccda}.columns p+p{margin-top:1rem}.steps ol{padding:0;border-top:1px solid var(--line);list-style:none}.steps li{display:grid;grid-template-columns:55px 1fr;gap:1rem;padding:1.35rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}.steps li>span{color:var(--blue);font-size:.8rem;font-weight:850}.steps h3{font-size:1.05rem}.steps p{max-width:690px;color:var(--ink-soft)}@media(max-width:780px){.proof{grid-template-columns:1fr}.proof article+article{border-left:0;border-top:1px solid var(--line)}.editorial{grid-template-columns:1fr;padding:1.6rem;gap:2rem}.columns{grid-template-columns:1fr}}</style>
